{#
  @file competitive_leakage_report.jinja2
  @description Renders a competitive wallet-share leakage report showing where
               a client's revenue is likely flowing to competitor banks or
               fintechs instead of through AfriFlow's platform.

               Each leakage item is a data-shadow signal derived from the
               DataShadowModel — a corridor or product gap where we expected
               to see activity but observed none.

               The report is intended for internal RM preparation and ExCo
               pipeline reviews, not for sharing with the client directly.

               Expected context variables:
                 client_name    — str: canonical client name
                 report_date    — str: ISO date of the reporting period
                 leakage_items  — list of leakage dicts, each containing:
                                    domain, country, description,
                                    estimated_revenue_gap_zar, urgency,
                                    recommended_action
                 total_leakage_zar — float: sum of all estimated gaps
  @author Thabo Kunene
  @created 2026-03-18
#}

{# ============================================================ #}
{# SECTION: Report header                                      #}
{# ============================================================ #}
{{ "=" * 70 }}
COMPETITIVE LEAKAGE REPORT: {{ client_name }}
Report Date: {{ report_date }}
{{ "=" * 70 }}

{# ============================================================ #}
{# SECTION: Introductory note                                  #}
{# Helps the RM understand what the report represents.         #}
{# ============================================================ #}
This report identifies revenue that should flow through our platform
but is likely going to competitors. Each item is derived from a
cross-domain data absence (data shadow) and represents an actionable
opportunity for the relationship team.

{{ "-" * 70 }}

{# ============================================================ #}
{# SECTION: Leakage item rows                                  #}
{# Sorted by urgency (HIGH first) in the generator layer.      #}
{# loop.index provides a 1-based item number.                  #}
{# ============================================================ #}
{% for item in leakage_items %}
{{ loop.index }}. [{{ item.urgency }}] [{{ item.domain | upper }}] {{ item.country }}
   Gap Description  : {{ item.description }}
   Estimated Leakage: R{{ "{:,.0f}".format(item.estimated_revenue_gap_zar) }} p.a.
   {# -------------------------------------------------------- #}
   {# Recommended action is the specific RM ask               #}
   {# -------------------------------------------------------- #}
   Recommended Action: {{ item.recommended_action }}
   {{ "-" * 60 }}
{% else %}
{# Fallback: rendered if no leakage items were detected        #}
  No competitive leakage detected for this client.
{% endfor %}

{# ============================================================ #}
{# SECTION: Summary totals                                     #}
{# ============================================================ #}
{{ "=" * 70 }}

{# Conditional: only show the total line if there are items to sum #}
{% if leakage_items %}
TOTAL ESTIMATED LEAKAGE: R{{ "{:,.0f}".format(total_leakage_zar) }} p.a.

{# ------------------------------------------------------------ #}
{# Count items by urgency so the RM can triage quickly          #}
{# ------------------------------------------------------------ #}
  High urgency items  : {{ leakage_items | selectattr("urgency", "equalto", "HIGH") | list | length }}
  Medium urgency items: {{ leakage_items | selectattr("urgency", "equalto", "MEDIUM") | list | length }}
{% else %}
TOTAL ESTIMATED LEAKAGE: R0
{% endif %}

{{ "=" * 70 }}
